e some numbers to ponder and then an idea to make them as awsome as they could be<br>
<br>
PoTG:<br>
1200 mana<br>
Group<br>
Castable on others<br>
Increase AC (24) <br>
Increase Hitpoints (450) <br>
Mana Regen (6 per tick) <br>
Max Duration:  1 hour 40 minutes <br>
<br>
Greater Familiar<br>
650 mana<br>
Self only<br>
+25 all resists<br>
Increase mana regen 4 a tick<br>
See invis<br>
Upon death of familiar wizard looses 50% of mana or if mana pool is empty health<br>
<br>
Is it just me, or does the familiar look extremely dissapointing in this light. Familiar is a huge liability to the wizard, and benefit we receive for such risk is virtually nil. +25 resists (extremely easy to reach 255 of any resist with proper buffs/equip) And see invis and 4mana a tick. Along with the vunerability to AE spells.<br>
<br>
When i first heard about familiars i assumed they would be true unique buffs, augmenting casting in a new way. Instead we get a buff with a graphic. Here's what i suggest<br>
<br>
Level 30/50/60 spell: Invoke lesser/greater/arch efficency<br>
Target<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> et<br>
Skill: conj<br>
Save: none<br>
duration: none<br>
cost: ??<br>
Augment Familiar, reduces cost of all offensive spells 10%/20%/30%<br>
<br>
Level 30/50/60 spell: Invoke lesser/greater/arch Wrath<br>
Target: pet<br>
Skill: Conj<br>
Save: none<br>
Duration: none<br>
cost: ??<br>
Augment familiar, increases damage of all offensive spells 15%/25%/35%<br>
<br>
Level 30/50/60 spell: Invoke lesser/greater/arch enticement<br>
Target:self<br>
Skill: conj<br>
Duration: none<br>
Cost: ??<br>
save:none<br>
Augment familiar, decreases resist rates 15/30/50% of all spells<br>
<br>
Level 30/50/60 spell: Invoke  lesser/greater/arch Recovery<br>
Target: Self<br>
Skill: conj<br>
Duration: none<br>
Cost: ??<br>
save:none<br>
Augment Familiar, increases mana and hp regeneration 5/10/15 points per tick<br>
<br>
Not stackable. You would have to change augments as the situation calls for, adding a nice level of variety and spice to the wizard class.<br>
<br>
Make them quest rewards. With a story and flavor to add to the game, not &quot;kill uber mobs A,B,C,D and then give me their rare drops&quot;<br>
<br>
This would add some much needed power and spice to wizards, and make familiars damn cool like we all thought they'd be. Post suggestions/comments/flames whatever =D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 380<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/12/01 10:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to make the familiar worthwhile, rather than a poor </span><hr size=1> Them being non-stackable makes this an idea that's actually worth passing on to VI, in my mind.  yeah, they become powerful, but with the weaknesses we get from having a buff that can HURT us when it leaves (what other buff does that?), being able to get a bit more is VERY nice.<br>
<br>
Question then: if you cast 1 of these &quot;augment&quot; spells and another is already there, do you overwrite the existing one, or fail on the new one?  I think for balance, we should have the new one fail, so that the familiar would have to be removed, then recast as well. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
