</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvalraukartarancalamon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valraukar TarAncalamon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/02 5:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The insanity goes on...</span><hr size=1> I've heard it all now.  Let's complain about everything, shall we?<br>
<br>
AoE kills your familiar?  Then don't summon it.  If you're on a raid level encounter where a mob is using massively harmful AoE, chances are you have plenty of support.  If the usual line of resist buffs, PoTG/KEI-C2/Flowing Thought/Bard Song, and Hp buffs aren't enough to keep you alive and fruitful, get out of that raid.  You're going to kill someone other than yourself and possibly everyone who is counting on you to do your job.  Your job on high level encounters?  You'd better know this already, but I'll spell it out:  DON'T out aggro the MA and ping pong the mob all over the place, DON'T overburn your mana too soon and leave the mob alive when everyone else has expened their mana and hps to get it to X% hps, DO nuke only when told to, and FINISH off the mob when it's time for you to do so.  Still want your familiar with you on such outings?  Put AA points into the class enhancement for it and make it immune.<br>
<br>
Now that raids are out of the way, let's address the single group--<br>
<br>
Familiar dies when you invis?  Eventually (we hope) this will no longer be an issue.  Verant has listed this as a known bug and table it to be fixed.  Until such time, a little forethought and planning goes a long way.  Don't summon the bloody thing until your at your particular camp spot.  If you need to invis in order to get there, chances are you're avoiding mobs rather than fighting them and a familiar isn't needed when one is evading.  Get to the camp, set up, summon your familiar and let the pulling begin.<br>
<br>
Mana regen is negligable?  Are you crazy?  If you can't maintain a mana pool during a regular ol' group, you're obviously a poor choice and should be dumped for someone else.  ANY mana regen is better than nothing, and familiar mana regen stacks with everything.  EVERYTHING!  KEI-C2/Flowing thought/Bard Song/PoTG.  If you need even more mana than even C2 alone can provide, again you are a poor choice and obviously in over your head.  I'll take any mana regen I can get, thanks.<br>
<br>
Fizzle rates aren't an issue?  That is just plain silly and bordering on reckless, IMHO.  I can't begin to name the times when I've tossed a stun on a mob to buy an enchanter a few extra seconds to re-cast a resisted stun, or to prevent a gate or CH from going off for that matter, only to have a fizzle kill my timing.  It's not often, but ANY reduction is more than welcome.  You don't use stuns, you say?  If you don't, it's because another player has that role covered, or you're an overburning agro-hound who can't deal with the adversity of playing multiple roles according to each unique scenario. =P<br>
<br>
Targeting is a pain with the flappy around?  If you don't have a hotkey for using /assist by now, please go back to soloing as you're not fit for any group over level 35.  Period.  Any enchanters or warriors out there disagree on that one?<br>
<br>
Forgive my rant, but I once looked forward to the release of the Translocational Suppression line--only to watch it go down in flames as message after message was sent to VI to burn it down.  How many other assets might we have today if all of us weren't demanding the full monty?  I understand that there may have been other issues surrounding the lack of help to our class, but I highly doubt that all the childish complaints sent to VI did much to encourage them.  <br>
<br>
In conclusion, shaddap, be creative, adapt to your surroundings, and make the most of what you DO have rather than complaining about it.  Could Familiars be better?  Certainly.  I could have a 10k mana pool and a 9:1 ratio nuke too, but I don't.<br>
<br>
