<br>
I look at the Pre-Kunark game, and I remember telling myself I am a Wizard I won't begin to shine until I have truly proven myself to the world. But then Kunark came out and that whole way of think was shot to hell! (And Velious only made me feel worse). But now we have Luclin and preceding that expansion's release we have a very long list of demands/requests/suggestions concerning our class. We wanted Mana regen, we wanted more mana (even if it were just a little) we wanted higher damage, we wanted a 'real' nuke for level 20, we wanted a level 60 nuke that was not a joke, we wanted to be able to offer something to our groups that did not involve teleports, some of us even wanted pets(what a joke), and the list just goes on and on and on.<br>
<br>
When Luclin came out we were given new spells (we won't talk about the O'keil line of spells... ever), and in the list of these new spells we find that we have a level 20 nuke that is actually useful (I even use it from time to time), we are given new teleport spells (though the function of these spells may require a rant of their own), and we have our much anticipated familiar spells. The level 29 familiar while not totally useless could be better. The level 49 familiar gave us a number of buff the most important of which was our much needed (and deserved) mana regen. Now on this point many complain that the mana regen is 'only' equivalent to FT1, and to that I say, sooooo? I personally feel that 1 mana per tick is better than the 0 mana per tick that we had before... The level 54 familiar (which I am using now) Is wonderful! 2 mana per tick (the same as breeze) resists, see invis, 75 mana added to our current mana pool, and some say that they also give 'random bursts of mana' (I haven't seen it nor I have read anything about that from Verant, so I won't mention it again). I won't talk about the 4 mana per tick or the 150 extra mana that the level 60 familiar gives since i don't have that one yet. Instead I will ask this... when will we be happy?<br>
<br>
Ok yes the familiars could be better as Valraukar stated, but who cares? Samantha (my familiar) works her butt off for me and in return I make her food, because she's a good little drake. When she gets lost she doesn't get into trouble, and when she finds me, she doesn't bring me all of the friend she met along the way. And to the people who think that she should be throwing out 'baby nukes' I say, 'Play a Mage!'<br>
<br>
Our teleports are not perfect. I was more than just a little upset about the Surefall Glade teleports, and yes, I am still bitter. I'm not happy that the Luclin teleports... Ok 'suck' is the word I'm looking for here. And the grouping requirement should be removed from the TLs. Though if just one of these things were fixed, I don't think I would complain 'openly' about our teleport spells. They are all fairly small issues if you consider the fact that it is a game, so I would be happy with one of these being fixed. But other would not, and you all know who you are.<br>
<br>
Our nukes aren't as good as they should be. Try reading a fantasy book that has a wizard in it, you will see that they do not show real power for quite some time. They struggle and endure for long periods of time, and many do not make it; but those who do become legends and sometimes even gods. I'm not saying that a level 60 Wizard is better that a level 60 of this class or that class, or that a level 60 Wizard could beat this person or that person in a duel, what I'm saying is that when it comes to doing what we do at that level, I challenge you to find a class.. AND class that does it better, or even as well as we do.<br>
<br>
Be proud of who you are. Solusek Ro has blessed you with a gift (even the disgraceful gnomes out there). We are very powerful and with that power must come an understanding. And if you do not understand, if you do not know your place, then you really should consider another class, and stop complaining about mine.<br>
<br>
(hmmm. This turned out much longer than I expected, sorry.)<br>
-Lunatari of Xegony<br>
