I also understand that this theoretical &quot;group balance&quot; doesn't always get acheived.  I do howver always find a way to be an asset or point blank tell the group that they should find someone else.  I'm here to play the game, enjoy it and the people I group with. <br>
<br>
If I snare a mob, I'm an asset.  If I stun a mob and prevent a CH or a gate from being cast, I'm an asset.  If I deliver the killing blow to a mob and saved even 30 seconds of fighting time, I'm an asset.  And yes, I will, and can, and HAVE done so for hours on end with no mana regen at all.  If I'm not enough of an asset to the group, most are straightforward enough to tell me so and I go my merry way without regret or hard feelings.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry your wizard isn't what you &quot;want&quot; or even maybe what you expect.  I didn't start playing a wizard with any preset notions on what I was &quot;supposed&quot; to be.  I took what I was given and made the most of it.  And the vast majority of the community on this board does also.<br>
<br>
But how many good ideas get trashed by our beloved community for no other reason than it's not what we &quot;expect&quot; or &quot;want&quot;?  I feel it's a valid question.  I don't think wizards couldn't use some fixing here and there, but I'm not going to trash what I have been given because it's not good enough.  It'll do until I'm given something better.<br>
